01:40.201 --> 01:41.569
[SCREECHES]

01:43.604 --> 01:45.373
Announcer: HOLA, RACE FANS.

01:45.439 --> 01:49.143
I'M HERRERA, COMING TO YOU
FROM VIEJO NUEVO, MEXICO.

01:49.210 --> 01:50.878
WHERE WE'RE MOMENTS
FROM THE START

01:50.944 --> 01:53.113
OF THE ENDURO-SLAM 5000--

01:53.181 --> 01:56.150
A 24 HOUR, BONE RATTLING
OFF ROAD RACE

01:56.217 --> 01:58.118
ACROSS TREACHEROUS DESERT.

01:58.186 --> 02:00.254
I'M HERE WITH
LOCAL DIRTBIKE LEGEND

02:00.321 --> 02:01.789
ROBERTO TORRES.

02:01.855 --> 02:04.057
HOW'S YOUR COMPETITION
LOOKING THIS YEAR, ROBERTO?

02:04.124 --> 02:05.326
PRETTY TOUGH, HYMIE.

02:05.393 --> 02:07.228
BUT ANYONE WHO ENTERS
THE ENDURO-SLAM

02:07.295 --> 02:09.029
HAS GOTTA BE GUTSY,
DETERMINED,

02:09.096 --> 02:10.998
AND ABSOLUTELY FEARLESS.

02:11.064 --> 02:12.600
[CAR BACKFIRES]
[BOTH GASP]

02:17.070 --> 02:18.806
ALL SET FOR THE RACE, GANG.

02:18.872 --> 02:20.541
GOSH,
I FEEL SO RUGGED.

02:20.608 --> 02:22.643
DOES THIS HELMET
CLASH WITH MY JUMPER?

02:22.710 --> 02:24.445
UH, NO.

02:24.512 --> 02:26.580
A 24 HOUR
OFF ROAD RACE--

02:26.647 --> 02:29.550
THIS HAS GOT TO BE
THE CRAZIEST THING
WE'VE EVER DONE--

02:29.617 --> 02:30.351
WILLINGLY.

02:30.418 --> 02:31.552
Fred: NO WORRIES, GANG.

02:31.619 --> 02:33.053
I'VE TRICKED OUT
THE MYSTERY MACHINE

02:33.120 --> 02:34.054
WITH EVERYTHING WE NEED

02:34.121 --> 02:35.122
FOR OFF ROAD
RACING--

02:35.189 --> 02:36.290
HIGHBOY SUSPENSION,

02:36.357 --> 02:37.358
BIG BOY RADIALS,

02:37.425 --> 02:38.959
BAD BOY HIGH BEAMS,

02:39.026 --> 02:40.294
IT'S ALL GOOD.

02:40.361 --> 02:41.895
DON'T FORGET
THE FAT BOY FRIDGE

02:41.962 --> 02:42.996
SCOOB AND I ADDED.

02:43.063 --> 02:44.131
IT'S, LIKE,
TOTALLY STOCKED.

02:44.198 --> 02:45.966
HA HA. WELL, IT WAS,

02:46.033 --> 02:48.502
BEFORE THAT LONG WAIT
AT THE BORDER.

02:48.569 --> 02:50.103
[LAUGHS]

02:50.170 --> 02:51.939
MMM. PAPAYA.

02:55.042 --> 02:59.347
HEY, IT'S 5 TIME
ENDURO-SLAM CHAMP
LUPE GESARES.

02:59.413 --> 03:01.249
YOU'RE
THE MAN, LUPE.

03:01.315 --> 03:02.983
SENORITA TO YOU.

03:03.050 --> 03:04.184
OH.

03:04.252 --> 03:06.053
WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR CAR?

03:06.119 --> 03:07.255
I WAS TAKING
A PRACTICE RUN

03:07.321 --> 03:09.523
WHEN I RAN INTO
THE GIANT WORM.

03:09.590 --> 03:10.491
[LAUGHS]

03:10.558 --> 03:12.960
SOUNDED LIKE SHE SAID
"GIANT WORM."

03:13.026 --> 03:14.462
THAT'S JUST RACER LINGO.

03:14.528 --> 03:15.763
RUNNING INTO
A GIANT WORM

03:15.829 --> 03:17.498
IS LIKE HITTING
THE WALL. RIGHT, LUPE?

03:17.565 --> 03:20.268
NO, IT'S LIKE RUNNING
INTO A GIANT WORM.

03:20.334 --> 03:22.370
EL GUSANO GRANDE.

03:22.436 --> 03:24.972
UM, IF THERE'S
A GIANT WORM OUT THERE,

03:25.038 --> 03:26.674
MAYBE THE RACE
SHOULD BE POSTPONED.

03:26.740 --> 03:29.176
YEAH. HEH HEH.
I SECOND THAT MOTION.

03:29.243 --> 03:31.745
EL GUSANO WILL NOT
STOP THE RACE

03:31.812 --> 03:35.516
OR STOP LUPE GESARES
FROM WINNING.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.184
[CHANTING]
OFF ROAD RACERS
EARTH DISGRACERS!

03:37.251 --> 03:40.754
OFF ROAD RACERS
EARTH DISGRACERS!...

03:40.821 --> 03:43.123
LOOKS LIKE A MONSTER WORM
ISN'T THE ONLY THING

03:43.190 --> 03:44.692
CAUSING PROBLEMS
AROUND HERE.

03:44.758 --> 03:47.328
A LOT OF FOLKS THINK
THESE TYPE OF RACES

03:47.395 --> 03:49.162
ARE BAD FOR
THE ENVIRONMENT.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.631
ALL THOSE GAS GUZZLERS.

03:50.698 --> 03:51.865
SO TRUE, VELMA.

03:51.932 --> 03:54.101
THAT'S WHY MY CAR'S
LUNAR POWERED.

03:54.167 --> 03:55.903
GIBBY NORTON?

03:55.969 --> 03:57.338
YOU TWO KNOW EACH OTHER?

03:57.405 --> 04:00.608
WE MET AT SCIENCE CAMP.
WE WERE LAB PARTNERS.

04:00.674 --> 04:02.676
IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU WANNA CALL IT.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.412
Fred: THAT'S
AN INTERESTING RIG,
FRIEND.

04:04.478 --> 04:06.880
LOOKS A LITTLE DELICATE
FOR OFF ROAD SURVIVAL,
THOUGH.

04:06.947 --> 04:07.948
WE'LL SEE ABOUT--

04:09.517 --> 04:11.552
SWEET RIDE, DUDE.

04:11.619 --> 04:14.087
THANKS. RIGHT BACK
AT 'CHA, FELLA.

04:14.154 --> 04:15.523
NAME'S BURT BATSON.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.257
WHAT KINDA HORSES YOU GOT?

04:17.325 --> 04:18.959
400 BIG ONES.

04:19.026 --> 04:21.094
NO, I MEANT REAL HORSES.

04:21.161 --> 04:23.263
'CAUSE YOU'RE
GONNA NEED 'EM
TO PULL THAT HEAP

04:23.331 --> 04:25.566
OUT OF THE DITCH
I'M GONNA DUMP IT IN.

04:25.633 --> 04:27.000
SEE YOU AT
THE FINISH LINE--

04:27.067 --> 04:29.002
NOT!
[LAUGHS]

04:42.015 --> 04:45.152
FRED, ARE YOU SURE
YOU'VE DRIVEN
OFF ROAD BEFORE?

04:45.218 --> 04:46.454
WELL, NOT EXACTLY.

04:46.520 --> 04:50.290
BUT I GOT A HIGH SCORE
IN VIDEO DIRT DEMON.

04:50.358 --> 04:51.425
FAST MOVE!

04:51.492 --> 04:53.927
I'M SUDDENLY VERY AFRAID.

04:56.163 --> 05:00.568
LOOKS LIKE THE FIRST CAR
THROUGH A PLACE CALLED
DIABLO GULCH WINS.

05:00.634 --> 05:01.769
DIABLO--

05:01.835 --> 05:03.471
ISN'T THAT SPANISH
FOR "DEVIL?"

05:03.537 --> 05:05.272
RELAX. WE GOT
A LONG WAY TO GO

05:05.339 --> 05:07.441
BEFORE WE GET
TO DIABLO GULCH.

05:07.508 --> 05:10.177
LOOK OUT!
IT'S THE MONSTER WORM!

05:10.243 --> 05:12.079
IT'S JUST AN
OLD STATUE, SHAGGY.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.715
Velma: ACTUALLY,
STATUES LIKE THAT
ARE COMMON HERE.

05:14.782 --> 05:16.350
THEY'RE A TRIBUTE
FROM ANCIENT FARMERS

05:16.417 --> 05:19.420
WHO RELIED ON WORMS
TO FERTILIZE
THE DESERT SOIL.

05:19.487 --> 05:23.323
HEY, I WONDER
IF THAT'S WHAT
LUPE GESARES RAN INTO?

05:25.092 --> 05:26.894
NO WAY TO FIND OUT NOW.

05:37.405 --> 05:39.640
I THINK THIS GUY
MASTERED VIDEO DIRT DEMON

05:39.707 --> 05:42.309
EVEN BETTER
THAN YOU DID, FRED.

05:42.376 --> 05:43.677
OR NOT.

05:48.382 --> 05:49.583
IF WE COULD PASS
THAT MOTORCYCLE,

05:49.650 --> 05:51.151
WE'LL BE IN THE LEAD.

05:51.218 --> 05:56.490
GREAT, AND ONLY
23 HOURS LEFT OF THIS
RAW ROAD RUDENESS.

05:56.557 --> 05:57.825
YEAH, ISN'T IT GREAT?

06:03.196 --> 06:04.798
HA! WE'VE GOT YOU--

06:04.865 --> 06:06.800
NOW?

06:06.867 --> 06:08.335
WHERE'D THEY GO?

06:08.402 --> 06:09.269
UP THERE!

06:09.336 --> 06:10.370
Both: HELP!

06:10.438 --> 06:12.139
HOW'D THEY GET
IN THAT TREE?

06:12.205 --> 06:14.408
[RUMBLING]

06:15.208 --> 06:16.810
All: AAH!

06:16.877 --> 06:18.846
[SCREECHES]

06:19.847 --> 06:20.848
[ALL GASP]

06:23.951 --> 06:25.453
[SCREECHING]

06:26.654 --> 06:28.422
WHO'S IN THE LEAD NOW?

06:28.489 --> 06:29.857
HA HA HA!

06:32.192 --> 06:34.562
LIKE, THE GIANT WORM
IS REAL.

06:34.628 --> 06:37.431
IT'S A DIFFERENT RACE
NOW, GANG.

06:37.498 --> 06:39.567
THERE'S A MYSTERY
WRIGGLING AROUND.

06:39.633 --> 06:41.935
GOOD THING THE WORM
ONLY POPPED A TIRE.

06:42.002 --> 06:44.071
HEY, WHERE'S THE JACK?

06:44.137 --> 06:45.806
OH, I HAD TO TAKE OUT THAT

06:45.873 --> 06:48.408
TO MAKE ROOM FOR A FEW EXTRA
OFF ROAD MODIFICATIONS.

06:48.476 --> 06:49.577
LIKE WHAT?

06:49.643 --> 06:51.712
HYDROLIC LIFTERS,
EJECTOR SEAT,

06:51.779 --> 06:53.514
EMERGENCY
FLOTATION DEVICE.

06:53.581 --> 06:55.549
WHY WOULD WE NEED
A FLOTATION DEVICE

06:55.616 --> 06:56.950
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE DESERT?

06:57.017 --> 06:59.653
WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN
A FLASH FLOOD MIGHT HIT.

06:59.720 --> 07:01.455
BESIDES, WHO NEEDS A JACK

07:01.522 --> 07:03.156
WHEN YOU'VE GOT
A FIRST RATE PIT CREW?

07:03.223 --> 07:04.157
HUH?
HUH?

07:04.224 --> 07:06.860
[BOTH GRUNTING]

07:06.927 --> 07:10.531
NOW I UNDERSTAND WHY
THEY CALL IT A "PIT CREW."

07:10.598 --> 07:14.301
HA HA HA.
LIKE, IT'S THE PITS.

07:14.367 --> 07:16.436
THERE. ALL DONE.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.473
[BOTH PANT, GASP]

07:19.540 --> 07:22.109
LIKE, IT'S THE WORM!

07:22.175 --> 07:24.945
Both: OW! OW! OW!
OOH! OW! OW! OW!

07:25.012 --> 07:28.048
GUYS, IT'S JUST A SHADOW
FROM SCOOBY'S TAIL.

07:28.115 --> 07:29.917
HA HA HA! OW!

07:35.589 --> 07:38.025
HEY, GOOD ONE,
SCOOB. OW!

07:41.795 --> 07:44.264
JUST ONE MORE, SCOOB.

07:44.331 --> 07:47.000
OW! SHEESH.

07:49.637 --> 07:51.972
Both: AAH! AAH! AAH!
OW! OW! OW!

07:56.944 --> 07:58.812
AAH! YEE-HAW!

07:58.879 --> 07:59.880
WHOA!

08:03.951 --> 08:06.654
JINKIES! IT'S CUTTING
RIGHT ACROSS THE RACE COURSE.

08:11.525 --> 08:13.226
I CAN MAKE IT.
I CAN MAKE IT.

08:14.427 --> 08:18.666
I WAS WRONG!

08:21.501 --> 08:23.203
All: PHEW!

08:23.270 --> 08:24.437
THAT WAS CLOSE.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.438
[CREAKS]

08:25.505 --> 08:27.507
EVERYONE
SLIDE FORWARD.

08:27.575 --> 08:29.610
NO, NO,
THE OTHER FORWARD!

08:33.146 --> 08:35.415
LIKE, LOOKS LIKE
THE RACE IS OVER--

08:35.482 --> 08:37.551
[WHIMPERS]
FOR US.

08:42.723 --> 08:43.891
All: AAH!

08:47.460 --> 08:50.530
WOW, THAT THING TOOK OFF
LIKE A JET.

08:50.598 --> 08:52.132
UNFORTUNATELY CATCHING US

08:52.199 --> 08:55.703
IN ITS TAIL WIND!

09:00.774 --> 09:04.477
WOW, YOUR FLOTATION DEVICE
ACTUALLY CAME IN HANDY.

09:04.544 --> 09:07.147
PONTOONS--DON'T
LEAVE HOME WITHOUT 'EM.

09:07.214 --> 09:09.950
LOOK, IT'S ROBERTO TORRES'
MOTORCYCLE.

09:10.017 --> 09:11.384
BUT WHERE IS HE?

09:11.451 --> 09:14.888
LIKE, MAYBE
THE GIANT WORM GOT HIM.

09:16.489 --> 09:18.058
[ALL WHIMPERING]

09:20.961 --> 09:23.196
Fred: HEY,
THE PROTESTERS WE SAW

09:23.263 --> 09:24.598
AT THE START OF THE RACE.

09:24.665 --> 09:26.399
WHAT ARE THEY DOING
DOWN HERE?

09:26.466 --> 09:28.368
WHAT ARE WE DOING
DOWN HERE?

09:28.435 --> 09:31.338
AND EXACTLY WHERE IS HERE?

09:31.404 --> 09:34.541
WHY, WORMTOPIA,
OF COURSE,

09:34.608 --> 09:40.714
THE ANCIENT HOME
OF THE GREAT WORM
GUSANO GRANDE.

09:40.781 --> 09:43.684
EL GUSANO.
EL GUSANO.

09:43.751 --> 09:45.919
WELL, WE'RE SORRY
FOR THE INTRUSION.

09:45.986 --> 09:47.888
BUT WE REALLY DO NEED
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

09:47.955 --> 09:51.992
[CHUCKLES]
WE'LL BE HAPPY TO
SHOW YOU THE WAY OUT

09:52.059 --> 09:55.528
AFTER THE GREAT
WORMIAN FEAST.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.097
THERE'S A FEAST?

09:57.164 --> 10:00.634
YES, AND YOU'RE
THE GUESTS OF HONOR.

10:00.701 --> 10:03.904
OH, GREAT WORM,

10:03.971 --> 10:07.107
ACCEPT THIS OFFERING
OF EVILDOERS

10:07.174 --> 10:10.043
WHO DARE TO DESICRATE
YOUR SACRED SHRINE

10:10.110 --> 10:13.313
WITH THEIR NASTY
OFF ROAD VEHICLES.

10:13.380 --> 10:15.182
LIKE,
THIS IS AN HONOR?

10:15.248 --> 10:18.318
NEVER TRUST ANYONE
WEARING A WORM SUIT.

10:18.385 --> 10:19.552
[SCREECH]
[GASPS]

10:19.619 --> 10:22.189
IT IS THE GREAT ONE.

10:22.255 --> 10:24.191
GUSANO LIVES!

10:24.257 --> 10:26.760
All: LONG LIVE THE WORM.

10:26.827 --> 10:30.764
LONG LIVE GUSANO GRANDE!

10:30.831 --> 10:32.766
LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE WORM FOOD.

10:32.833 --> 10:34.034
THERE'S A TUNNEL
OUT OF HERE.

10:34.101 --> 10:36.670
BUT WE'LL NEVER GET PAST
THESE WORM DUDES.

10:36.737 --> 10:38.806
UNLESS WE CAN
DISTRACT THEM SOMEHOW.

10:38.872 --> 10:41.942
HEH. TOO BAD WE DON'T HAVE
AN EARLY BIRD TO GET THE WORM.

10:42.009 --> 10:44.311
HEY, LIKE,
WHO SAYS WE DON'T?

10:44.377 --> 10:45.378
[WHISPERS]

10:47.247 --> 10:49.382
Scooby: CAW! CAW!

10:49.449 --> 10:50.718
All: AAH!

10:52.352 --> 10:53.286
WHAT?

10:53.353 --> 10:55.388
Scooby: CAW! CAW!

10:59.026 --> 11:02.295
OH, HA HA.
HOW DO YOU
DO THAT, SCOOB?

11:21.782 --> 11:23.316
[MAN SINGING IN SPANISH]

12:40.327 --> 12:41.561
[SCREECHES]

12:41.628 --> 12:43.230
Both: WHOA!

12:50.537 --> 12:52.405
[SCREECHES]

12:56.243 --> 12:58.145
LOOKS LIKE WE'RE STILL
IN THE RACE.

12:58.211 --> 13:01.181
GRACIAS, AMIGOS.
YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

13:01.248 --> 13:02.615
[ALL SCREAM]

13:02.682 --> 13:04.417
OH!

13:10.523 --> 13:11.724
HEY, WATCH IT.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.927
YOU SCRATCHED MY CAR.

13:16.629 --> 13:18.031
THE HALFWAY POINT
OF THE RACE.

13:18.098 --> 13:19.799
WE'D BETTER FILL UP.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.804
YOU HEARD THE MAN, SCOOB.

13:24.872 --> 13:27.540
2 BOWLS OF BEANS,
PLEASE.

13:27.607 --> 13:28.842
REAH.

13:35.949 --> 13:37.517
THOSE CREEPY
WORM WORSHIPPERS

13:37.584 --> 13:41.054
AREN'T THE ONLY ONES
TRYING TO GET RID
OF THE COMPETITION.

13:41.121 --> 13:43.756
I'M SURPRISED
YOU MADE IT THIS FAR.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.292
YOU'RE TOUGHER
THAN YOU LOOK.

13:45.358 --> 13:48.595
WELL, NOT TO BOAST,
BUT I CAN BENCH 220.

13:51.498 --> 13:54.301
GIBBY? YOU MADE IT
ACROSS THAT FISSURE?

13:54.367 --> 13:55.568
PIECE OF CAKE,

13:55.635 --> 13:57.837
EXCEPT I SPRUNG
A RADIATOR LEAK
IN THE PROCESS.

13:57.905 --> 13:59.272
THAT'S A TOUGH BREAK,
BUDDY.

13:59.339 --> 14:01.208
YOU'LL NEVER GET
A NEW RADIATOR OUT HERE.

14:01.274 --> 14:03.944
DON'T NEED ONE.
MY CAR HAS AN ENGINE
IN THE FRONT

14:04.011 --> 14:05.445
AND ONE IN THE REAR.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.414
IT'S DESIGNED TO BE DRIVEN
FROM EITHER END.

14:07.480 --> 14:09.216
WOW, PRETTY COOL.

14:09.282 --> 14:12.619
YOU TALKIN' ABOUT
THE CAR OR ME?

14:15.555 --> 14:19.326
GOSH, WE WERE
REALLY LOW ON FUEL.

14:19.392 --> 14:21.895
COME ON, GUYS.
WE'RE ALL GASSED UP.

14:21.962 --> 14:22.829
YEAH, SO ARE...

14:22.896 --> 14:24.898
DON'T EVEN.

14:34.607 --> 14:36.076
Fred: WE'RE OUT OF GAS.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.948
SOMEONE SABOTAGED
OUR FUEL TANK.

14:41.014 --> 14:43.183
WE'D BETTER GET BACK
TO THE GAS STATION.

14:44.817 --> 14:46.053
[SCREECHES]

14:48.788 --> 14:50.057
Shaggy: OR NOT.

14:56.229 --> 14:58.265
WHOA!

14:58.331 --> 14:59.967
AAH!

15:00.033 --> 15:01.301
[ALL WHIMPER]

15:05.905 --> 15:09.176
ZOINKS! LIKE, HOW ARE WE
GONNA WORM OUR WAY
OUT OF THIS ONE?

15:09.242 --> 15:11.378
QUICK,
POP THE HOOD.

15:12.179 --> 15:14.581
BATTERY, WATER...

15:17.284 --> 15:18.618
BOBBY PIN.

15:22.755 --> 15:23.690
[ENGINE STARTS]

15:23.756 --> 15:24.791
VOILA.

15:24.857 --> 15:25.993
WOW, DAPHNE,

15:26.059 --> 15:27.794
A HYDRO ELECTRIC
FUEL SOURCE

15:27.860 --> 15:29.429
FROM THINGS FOUND
IN YOUR PURSE.

15:29.496 --> 15:30.530
NO BIGGIE.

15:36.869 --> 15:40.707
HEY, DID YOU GUYS
SEE HOW THE WORM
WENT AROUND THE ROCK?

15:40.773 --> 15:42.442
HMM.

15:42.509 --> 15:43.943
HUH? AH.

15:45.878 --> 15:46.879
[TIRES SCREECH]

15:46.946 --> 15:48.681
WE'RE SAFE UP HERE.

15:48.748 --> 15:51.551
IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
IT CAN BURROW THROUGH
SOLID ROCK.

15:51.618 --> 15:54.087
LOOK--
DIABLO GULCH.

15:54.154 --> 15:56.956
Fred: THE FINISH LINE
IS THROUGH
THAT NARROW CANYON.

16:04.497 --> 16:08.035
BE MY GUEST,
HEH, HEH, HEH.

16:20.313 --> 16:21.748
THAT WORM'S
GONNA WASTE HIM.

16:21.814 --> 16:22.749
WE'D BETTER ROLL.

16:22.815 --> 16:23.983
[TIRES SCREECH]

16:37.164 --> 16:39.432
HEY! WE'RE TRYING
TO HELP YOU, PAL!

16:39.499 --> 16:43.336
NAH-UH. YOU'RE JUST TRYIN'
TO GET TO DIABLO GULCH FIRST.

16:47.174 --> 16:48.875
DAPHNE,
TAKE THE WHEEL.

16:48.941 --> 16:50.543
CAREFUL, FREDDY.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.465
LOOK WHAT YOU DID
TO MY RIDE!

17:12.532 --> 17:14.201
[SCREECHING]

17:16.436 --> 17:18.705
YEE-HAW!

17:21.874 --> 17:24.944
LIKE, PLEASE--DON'T SAY
WE'RE GOIN' AFTER THAT GUY.

17:25.011 --> 17:26.846
THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO FOR HIM.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.315
BUT WE CAN
STOP THAT WORM

17:28.381 --> 17:30.350
BEFORE IT HURTS
ANY OTHER RACERS.

17:30.417 --> 17:31.618
[WHIMPERS]

17:33.720 --> 17:35.155
OKAY, HERE'S THE PLAN:

17:35.222 --> 17:37.056
THE ENGINE SOUND
SHOULD ATTRACT THE WORM.

17:37.124 --> 17:38.491
NOW WHEN IT COMES OUT,

17:38.558 --> 17:39.892
YOU GUYS LEAD IT
INTO THE GULCH.

17:39.959 --> 17:40.893
YOU READY?

17:40.960 --> 17:42.362
Both: UH-UH.

17:42.429 --> 17:44.997
WHAT'S THAT?
CAN'T HEAR YOU
OVER THE ENGINE NOISE.

17:45.064 --> 17:47.634
[TIRES SQUEAL]

17:51.104 --> 17:53.606
Both: AAH!

17:56.809 --> 17:58.545
Both: AAH!

17:58.611 --> 18:00.747
[SCREECHES]

18:00.813 --> 18:03.483
Both: AAH!

18:09.489 --> 18:12.425
HEY, FRED'S PLAN
ACTUALLY WORKED.

18:13.860 --> 18:14.794
[SCREECHES]

18:14.861 --> 18:18.698
ZOINKS!
WHO CUT THE NET?

18:18.765 --> 18:21.868
All: LONG LIVE GUSANO!

18:21.934 --> 18:24.471
THE WORMIANS, OF COURSE.

18:24.537 --> 18:26.206
[SCREECHING]

18:31.144 --> 18:33.112
FRED, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING?

18:35.148 --> 18:37.417
[TIRES SQUEAL]

18:40.687 --> 18:42.222
[HISSES]

18:43.856 --> 18:45.692
All: HAIL THE WORM.

18:47.760 --> 18:50.363
[TIRES SQUEAL]

18:58.805 --> 19:01.140
NO! FREDDY!

19:04.944 --> 19:07.780
All: AAH!

19:07.847 --> 19:10.350
Both: AAH! AAH!

19:11.184 --> 19:12.952
[BOTH GRUNT]

19:13.019 --> 19:15.555
JEEPERS!
WHERE'D HE GO?

19:16.956 --> 19:18.725
I DON'T REMEMBER
A SUNROOF.

19:20.427 --> 19:22.662
IT'S PART OF
THE EJECTOR SEAT SYSTEM
I INSTALLED.

19:22.729 --> 19:24.096
PRETTY STYLIN', HUH?

19:24.163 --> 19:26.433
HELP! HELP!

19:28.268 --> 19:29.101
Velma:
COME ON OUT...

19:29.168 --> 19:30.169
GIBBY.

19:30.237 --> 19:32.605
All: GIBBY NORTON?

19:32.672 --> 19:34.741
LIKE, HOW DID YOU KNOW
IT WAS HIM, VELMA?

19:34.807 --> 19:37.577
I FIGURED THE WORM
HAD TO BE A RACER.

19:37.644 --> 19:39.612
BECAUSE IT ALWAYS
WENT AFTER THE LEADER.

19:39.679 --> 19:40.913
IT WANTED TO WIN.

19:40.980 --> 19:43.683
MY FIRST CLUE WAS
THIS PIECE OF WORM TOOTH.

19:43.750 --> 19:44.717
IT'S BLACK GLASS

19:44.784 --> 19:47.620
LIKE THE LUNAR PANELS
ON GIBBY'S CAR.

19:47.687 --> 19:49.689
THEN THE WORM
OOZED GREEN STUFF

19:49.756 --> 19:51.458
JUST LIKE THE FLUID
FROM HIS RADIATOR.

19:51.524 --> 19:53.393
I DIDN'T WANNA
HURT ANYONE.

19:53.460 --> 19:54.561
I JUST WANTED
TO IMPRESS VELMA

19:54.627 --> 19:55.928
WITH MY SUPER COOL
WORM MOBILE.

19:55.995 --> 19:58.598
YOU MEAN,
YOU DID IT FOR ME?

19:58.665 --> 20:00.900
YEP, AND I WOULD HAVE
GOTTEN AWAY WITH IT,

20:00.967 --> 20:03.670
IF NOT FOR YOU MEDDLING
OFF THE ROAD RACERS.

20:06.773 --> 20:08.275
SO WHO WON THE RACE?

20:08.341 --> 20:10.477
ACTUALLY, NO ONE DID.

20:10.543 --> 20:13.413
WITH THE GULCH BLOCKED,
YOU'D HAVE TO GO ON FOOT.

20:14.781 --> 20:15.815
RUN FOR IT!

20:15.882 --> 20:17.784
[ALL LAUGH, CHATTER]

20:27.694 --> 20:30.630
JINKIES! SCOOBY WON!
[CHEERS]

20:34.000 --> 20:36.703
SCOOBY-OOBY-OOBY-OOBY

20:36.769 --> 20:38.571
SCOOBY DOO!
